api endpoint

auth
POST /auth/register
1. Validate request body
2. Check if email exists
3. Check if username exists
4. Hash password
5. Create user
6. Generate access token
7. Generate refresh token
8. Save refresh token
9. Return user and tokens

POST /auth/login
1. Validate request body
2. Find user by email
3. Check if user exists
4. Compare password with passwordHash
5. Generate access token
6. Generate refresh token
7. Save refresh token
8. Return user and tokens

POST /auth/logout
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate request body
3. Find refresh token
4. Verify it belongs to the user
5. Revoke or delete refresh token
6. Return success response

POST /auth/refresh-token
1. Validate request body
2. Find refresh token in database
3. Check if token exists
4. Check if token is revoked
5. Check if token is expired
6. Verify JWT refresh token
7. Find user
8. Generate new access token
9. Return access token

POST /auth/forgot-password
1. Validate request body
2. Find user by email
3. If user exists:
   - Generate reset token
   - Save hashed reset token and expiry
   - Send email with reset link
4. Always return success response

POST /auth/reset-password
1. Validate request body
2. Hash the reset token
3. Find user with matching passwordResetToken
4. Check passwordResetExpires
5. Hash new password
6. Update user's passwordHash
7. Clear passwordResetToken
8. Clear passwordResetExpires
9. Revoke all refresh tokens for the user
10. Return success response

POST /auth/change-password
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate request body
3. Find user
4. Compare currentPassword with passwordHash
5. If incorrect, throw error
6. Hash newPassword
7. Update passwordHash
8. Revoke all refresh tokens
9. Return success response

POST /auth/verify-email
1. Validate request body
2. Hash token
3. Find user with matching verification token
4. Check token expiry
5. Set isVerified = true
6. Clear verification token
7. Clear verification expiry
8. Return success response

user
GET /users/me
1. Authenticate user
2. Extract userId from JWT
3. Find user by id
4. Return user profile

PATCH /users/me
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate body
3. Get userId from JWT
4. Check username conflict (if changing)
5. Update user fields
6. Return updated user
DELETE /users/me
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate password
3. Get userId from JWT
4. Check password matches
5. Delete user's refresh tokens
6. Remove user data
7. Handle owned workspaces
8. Return success response

POST /users/me/avatar
1. Authenticate user
2. Receive image file
3. Validate file type/size
4. Upload to storage
5. Get image URL
6. Update user's profilePicture
7. Return updated user

GET /users/search
id="h8r8sc"
1. Authenticate user
2. Get search query
3. Search username/email/name
4. Exclude sensitive fields
5. Return matching users

workspace
GET /workspaces/:workspaceId
1. Authenticate user
2. Get userId from JWT
3. Get workspaceId from params
4. Check workspace exists
5. Check user is a member of workspace
6. Return workspace data

GET /workspaces
1. Authenticate user
2. Get userId from JWT
3. Find WorkspaceMember records by userId
4. Get related workspaces
5. Return workspaces

POST /workspaces
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate body
3. Get userId from JWT
4. Generate inviteCode
5. Create workspace
6. Set ownerId = userId
7. Create WorkspaceMember record
8. Set role = OWNER
9. Return workspace

DELETE /workspaces/:workspaceId
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate workspaceId
3. Find workspace
4. Check user is workspace owner
5. Delete workspace
6. Delete workspace members
7. Delete projects
8. Delete tasks
9. Delete comments
10. Delete activity logs
11. Return success

PATCH /workspaces/:workspaceId
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate workspaceId
3. Check workspace exists
4. Check user is OWNER/ADMIN
5. Update allowed fields
6. Create ActivityLog
7. Return updated workspace

POST /workspaces/join
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate inviteCode
3. Find workspace by inviteCode
4. Check workspace exists
5. Check user is not already a member
6. Create WorkspaceMember
7. Set role = MEMBER
8. Create ActivityLog
9. Return workspace

POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/leave
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate workspaceId
3. Find workspace
4. Check user is a member
5. Check user is not owner
6. Remove WorkspaceMember record
7. Create ActivityLog
8. Return success

DELETE/workspaces/:workspaceId/members/: memberId
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate params
3. Find workspace
4. Check requester role
5. Find member in WorkspaceMember
6. Check target is not owner
7. Delete WorkspaceMember record
8. Create ActivityLog
9. Return success

POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/invite
1. Authenticate user
2. Validate params/body
3. Find workspace
4. Check requester role
5. Find invited user
6. Check user is not already a member
7. Create WorkspaceMember
8. Set role = MEMBER
9. Create ActivityLog
10. Return success

